 sequence of interlinked poems, Haiku for a Season reveals Zanzotto also as a master poet of minimalism. Zanzotto’s recent death is a blow to world poetry, and the publication of this book, the last that he approved in manuscript, will be an event in both the United States and in Italy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aPOETRY / General.2bisacsh  ahaiku, poetry, italy, literature, creative writing, women, gender, life stages, seasons, nature, ecofeminism, youth, femininity, adulthood, landscape, bilingual, minimalism, simplicity, metaphor, contemporary, sister, family, beauty, love, passion, sexuality, coming of age, summer, wind, weather, hail, storm, poppy, ocean, water, flowers, insects.1 aBarron, Patrick, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSecco, Anna, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226922225423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226922225/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles